  <bioghist id="aspace_7ffb55d234abd0e28240d13846525f7d">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Amos B. Stanton of Adrian, N.Y. (Steuben County) served as a 1st lieutenant in the 86th Regiment, New York Volunteers, an Elmira, N.Y. regiment. He was killed at Petersburg on June 16, 1864.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_19836bd2bfa60fdf12e5c672bff8dcc6">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Primarily Civil War letters from Stanton to his wife. Also, family letters, certificates, pension files, clippings, publications, and diaries of John Crosby and Amos B. Stanton.</p>  </scopecontent>
